h3. Issue Summary
When inputting a text into Rich Text Editor, on the Text tab the *Dollar ($)* symbol next to some notation (see the attached example), it lost the format when changed to the Visual bar.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Create a new comment;
# Create a NoFormat, quote or code box;
# Click on the *Text* tab;
# Write the text with *$*;
# Change to *Visual* tab to check it.

 [^sup_demo.mp4] 

h3. Expected Results
Formatting will be kept when going to *Visual* tab.

h3. Actual Results
Formatting parameters are being lost when writing a *Dollar ($)* Symbol next a the notation.
 
h3. Workaround
# Create a new comment;
# Create a NoFormat, quote or code box;
# Click on the *Text* tab;
# Write the text with *$*;
** put a space between *$* and end of notation;
** do a breakline after the *$*;
# Change to *Visual* tab to check it.

